{
  "stem": "12494.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There five, six, seven of us who did that together.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And one of the ones who was with me in, I believe, 1942, was one of the survivors of the [INAUDIBLE] Massacre.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And so I learned about that going on.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And, of course, one knew about-- about the anti-Jewish legislation, about the fact that the majority of the Jewish population was unemployed, because the employment rules were such that Jews could be employed only in limited numbers.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So particularly the white collar and educated Jews became unemployed.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "You heard about that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "There were supporting activities.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And, of course, in our case, my father was [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] chairman of the Orthodox Rescue Committee, which was called [NON-ENGLISH] in Budapest, which was available to receive Jewish refugees from the surrounding countries.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "That is, no longer Austria-- that was long over by that time-- but Slovakia, the occupied portions of [INAUDIBLE] and Soviet Union, Romania, and Yugoslavia.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Hungary became a haven for Jewish refugees.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The Hungarian government was not bloody.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "The Hungarian government was after money, and they deprived Jews of their livelihood to a large extent.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "They ostensibly cooperated with the Germans, and they did cooperate with the Germans.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But in Jewish matters, they refused to be bloody.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So thousands and thousands of Jewish refugees congregated in Hungary, and my father was the Orthodox head-- was the head of the Orthodox organization, which supported these people.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was away from home much of the time, but as of March or April, 1942, I was at home.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so I saw the stream of these people coming, and I gradually became quite involved.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
